            {
                "content": "Great \u2014 the sensible \u201cnext step\u201d is to package this into a clean, reproducible solve script.\n\nI\u2019d use this one-liner script (save as `solve_hybrid2.py`):\n\n```python\n#!/usr/bin/env python3\nimport gmpy2\nimport base64\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom cryptography.fernet import Fernet\n\n# Load values\nvals = {}\nfor line in Path(\"/home/ctfplayer/ctf_files/values.txt\").read_text().strip().splitlines():\n    k, v = line.split(\":\")\n    vals[k] = int(v)\n\nns = [vals[f\"n{i}\"] for i in range(1, 5)]\ncs = [vals[f\"c{i}\"] for i in range(1, 5)]\ne = vals[\"e\"]\n\n# CRT: reconstruct m^e\nN = 1\nfor n in ns:\n    N *= n\n\nx = 0\nfor n, c in zip(ns, cs):\n    m_i = N // n\n    inv = gmpy2.invert(m_i, n)\n    x = (x + c * m_i * inv) % N\n\n# e-th root\nm, exact = gmpy2.iroot(x, e)\nif not exact:\n    raise RuntimeError(\"Root not exact; attack assumptions failed\")\n\n# Decode message bytes (the random password)\nh = hex(int(m))[2:]\nif len(h) % 2:\n    h = \"0\" + h\npassword = bytes.fromhex(h)\nprint(\"[+] Recovered password:\", password.decode())\n\n# Decrypt Fernet token\ntoken = Path(\"/home/ctfplayer/ctf_files/encrypted_flag.txt\").read_text().strip().encode()\nfernet_key = base64.urlsafe_b64encode(password)\nflag = Fernet(fernet_key).decrypt(token)\nprint(\"[+] Flag:\", flag.decode())\n```\n\nRun:\n```bash\npython3 solve_hybrid2.py\n```\n\nExpected output includes:\n- recovered password: `xYDFDoqcOACPKeT5gT0wBzAfBSoGieVc`\n- flag: `flag{u5e_b1gg3r_e_pl34s3}`\n\nIf you want, I can also generate a short CTF writeup format (Challenge \u2192 Vulnerability \u2192 Exploit \u2192 Flag) ready to submit.",
